A CYCLIST has been left seriously injured after colliding with a car.&nbsp;The female cyclist, said to be in her 30s, was taken to the Victoria hospital after the collision on Cathcart Road at Queen's Road.The accident happened around 8pm yesterday, leaving the woman with broken bones but not in a life-threatening condition.She was treated and later released from the hospital.A police spokeswoman said: &quot; The woman was treated and released and a 30-year-old man is the subject fo a report to the fiscal in connection with alleged road traffic offences.&quot;